title.narrative: 501 POLICY AND PLANNING FOR EQUITABLE QUALITY EDUCATION

description.narrative: National and state governments have increased capacity for coordination and evidence based policies, planning, implementation and monitoring for equitable, inclusive and risk informed quality education, which contributes to Access To Quality Learning Opportunities, Access To Quality Learning Opportunities (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Community Engagement, Social And Behaviour Change, Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Partnerships And Engagement: Public And Private, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Business and Key Business Stakeholders demonstrate growing willingness, commitment and resource allocation for protecting and promoting child rights in policy and practice by 2022

title.narrative: National and state governments have increased capacity for coordination and evidence based policies, planning, implementation andmonitoring for equitable, inclusive and risk informed quality education

description.narrative: Twelve state states utilized gender and equity-based analysis with Educational Management Information System (EMIS) education indicators leading to improve use of data and evidence in preparation and monitoring of Samagra Shiksha (SS) education sector annual plans. UNICEFs technical support to Ministry of Education (MoE) and National Council of Educational Research and Training (NCERT) in the development of assessment framework, sampling design, item development and pilot analysis led to the design and roll out of ;National Achievement Survey (NAS) 2021 in 118,000 schools covering 3.6 million students ;across the country which will provide data on COVID-19 impact on learning | Status:On-track | As-of Date:09/01/2022
